-- Pao de Acucar, Ripley, Telefonos de Mexico: Latin America Equity Preview
-- Nathan Gill
-- 2010-07-05T06:17:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/pao-de-acucar-ripley-telefonos-de-mexico-latin-america-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Latin American trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous
close.  
 The  MSCI Latin America Index  rose 1.8 percent to 3,710.87.
In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-traded class of
stock.  
 Brazil  
 Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao Grupo Pao de Acucar  (PCAR5
BZ): Brazil’s biggest retailer expects to “make savings” from
the takeover of Casa Bahia Comercial Ltda. by 2011, Chief
Executive Officer  Eneas Pestana  said in a conference call. The
shares fell 0.5 percent to 63.2 reais.  
 Chile  
 Ripley Corp SA  (RIPLEY CC): The Santiago-based department-
store operator said a block of company shares will be auctioned
on the Santiago exchange at 12:30 p.m. New York time on July 5.
Corp Capital Corredores de Bolsa SA will offer 96.8 million
Ripley shares at a minimum price of 530 pesos each, or a total
of $95.5 million, according to a statement posted by the
exchange. The shares fell 1.3 percent to 567.61 pesos.  
 Mexico  
 Telefonos de Mexico SAB  (TELMEXL MM): Mexico’s largest
phone company said it re-established 80 percent of service lost
after Hurricane Alex hit northeastern Mexico June 30. The impact
on telephone service was minor, Telmex, as the Mexico City-based
company is known, said in an e-mail. The shares rose 0.9 percent
to 9.34 pesos.  
